<DOC><DOCNO> AP890423-0028 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-23-89 1204EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Bangladesh-Cancer     04-23 0122</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Bangladesh-Cancer,0124</SECOND><HEAD>Most Bangladeshi Cancer Victims Die Without Treatment</HEAD><DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Two thirds of more than 200,000Bangladeshis who develop cancer each year fail to receive propertreatment and eventually die of the disease, news reports andofficials said Sunday.   ``Cancer is taking a heavy toll every year with little medicaltreatment available for the victims,'' said Dr. Abdul Hye, head ofthe Cancer Institute of Bangladesh.   United News of Bangladesh news agency, quoting World HealthOrganization officials in Dhaka, said the country now has more than800,000 cancer victims. It said most were unaware of their illness.   Bangladesh, which has a population of 110 million people, hasonly four major hospitals with facilities for detecting andtreating cancer.</TEXT></DOC>